}To perform a static cast, we start with thestatic_castkeyword, and then place the type to convert to inside angled brackets. Then inside parenthesis, we place the expression whose value will be converted. Note how much the syntax looks like a function call to a function namedstatic_cast<type>()with the expression whose value will be converted provided as an argument! Static casting a value to another type of value returns a temporary object that has been direct-initialized with the converted value.Here’s how we’d usestatic_castto solve the problem we introduced in the introduction of this lesson:#include <iostream>

int main()
{
